Because $A, B, C$ are angles of a triangle, none of them can be obtuse. Also, $\sin{A} = \dfrac{3}{5} < \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}} = \sin\left(\dfrac{\pi}{4}\right)$. Hence, $A < \dfrac{\pi}{4}$ and $\cos{A} > \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}} > \dfrac{7}{25}$. Therefore, $\cos{A} = \dfrac{4}{5}$, and the Law of Cosines gives \begin{align*}\cos{C} &= \cos\left(\pi - (A + B)\right) &&= -\cos{A}\cos{B} + \sin{A}\sin{B}\\ &= -\left(\dfrac{4}{5}\right)\left(\dfrac{7}{25}\right) + \left(\dfrac{3}{5}\right)\left(\dfrac{24}{25}\right)\\ &= \dfrac{48 - 28}{125}\\ \sin{C} &= \sqrt{1 - \left(\dfrac{16}{125}\right)^2} &&= \boxed{\dfrac{119}{125}}\end{align*}</answer>

